Description: Fix CVE-2020-7676 - angular.js jqLite XHTML sanitization bypass
 angular.js prior to 1.8.0 allows cross site scripting. The regex-based input
 HTML replacement in jqLiteBuildFragment() may turn sanitized code into unsanitized
 one. This patch introduces the UNSAFE_restoreLegacyJqLiteXHTMLReplacement opt-in,
 gates the XHTML self-closing tag replacement behind JQLite.legacyXHTMLReplacement,
 and rebuilds table wrapper elements via DOM APIs (modern browsers) instead of the
 XHTML string replacement path. Backported from the upstream 1.8.0 fix; transplanted
 from the internally-validated angular 1.4.14 patch onto the flat npm-published
 angular@1.3.0 bundle (angular.js at package root).
